.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/paul-mccartney-bass-guitar-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/paul-mccartney-bass-guitar-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/paul-mccartney-bass-guitar-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>数百人与全球搜索呼吁的组织者取得联系，以帮助找到<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/paul-mccartney">保罗·麦卡特尼 (Paul McCartney)</a>的原创赫夫纳 (Höfner) 贝斯吉他。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/live/paul-mccartney-live-at-glastonbury-2022-setlist-photos-review-3255717">Paul McCartney 在 Glastonbury 2022 现场直播：与 The Boss 一起创造摇滚历史</a></strong></li></ul><p><a href="https://thelostbass.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lost Bass</a>项目呼吁提供有关“历史上最重要的贝斯”的信息，这是<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-beatles">披头士乐队</a>明星购买的第一把贝斯，他于 1961 年在德国汉堡以 30 英镑（38 美元）的价格购买了这把贝斯。</p><p>然而，它于 1969 年 1 月消失，当时披头士乐队在伦敦录制“Get Back/Let It Be”的录音。</p><p>根据 The Lost Bass Project 的说法，失踪的 Höfner 500/1 小提琴贝斯是在《Love Me Do》、《She Loves You》和《Twist and Shout》中可以听到的一把。</p><p>负责搜寻工作的是赫夫纳的尼克·沃斯，他与丈夫和妻子团队斯科特·琼斯和内奥米·琼斯合作，他们都是记者和电视制片人。</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">欢迎来到“失落的贝斯项目”——全球寻找保罗·麦卡特尼的原创赫夫纳贝斯。 1961 年至 1969 年间，这款贝斯改变了世界。今天它是摇滚乐的圣杯。追踪。并帮助追踪低音。访问<a href="https://t.co/4eZFkyULMv">https://t.co/4eZFkyULMv</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/TracingTheBass?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@tracingthebass</a> <a href="https://t.co/VauQW8G9bB">pic.twitter.com/VauQW8G9bB</a></p><p> — TracingTheBass (@TracingTheBass) <a href="https://twitter.com/TracingTheBass/status/1697951309523980712?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 9 月 2 日</a></p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p>沃斯告诉<em><a href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-66700300" target="_blank" rel="noopener">英国广播公司</a></em>，麦卡特尼在最近的一次谈话中向他询问了这把吉他的情况，从而启动了寻找这把吉他的工作。 “目前尚不清楚它被存放在哪里，也不清楚谁可能在那里，”他说。 “对于大多数人来说，他们会记住它……正是贝斯造就了披头士乐队。”</p><p> Scott first became interested in the guitar&#39;s whereabouts after watching McCartney headline <a href="https://www.nme.com/glastonbury">Glastonbury</a> last year.</p><p> He approached Höfner only to discover they were already having conversations about tracking it down: “Paul said to Höfner &#39;surely if anyone can find this guitar, it&#39;s you guys&#39;, and that&#39;s how it all came about,” Scott said.</p><p> “Now we&#39;re working together on this. Nick has more technical knowledge about this guitar than anyone on the planet, and me and my Naomi are bringing some investigative skills.”</p><p> Since the project launched on Saturday (September 2), the team has already received hundreds of emails, with Scott telling PA news that two in particular were picked out because the information “instantly marries up with something that was known before”.</p><p> “We didn&#39;t expect to get necessarily thousands of super-hot leads instantly… what I&#39;m anticipating is that people who know something will probably just sort of reflect on what they know and then come forward at some point,” he added.</p><p> Asked whether he could share detailed of the leads, he said he could not provide a name of someone mentioned by “different people”.</p><p> “The name [has] cropped up a few times now, because it&#39;s disconnected and it&#39;s coming from a range of sources. Obviously, things like that stand out,” he said.</p><p> The investigative journalist added that it was possible someone could “innocently” own the bass “without realising what they&#39;ve got”.</p><p> He added that it&#39;s “worth looking at the <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/john-lennon">John Lennon</a> acoustic guitar” that he used to write &#39;I Want To Hold Your Hand&#39;.</p><p> “That guitar was stolen from a Beatles Christmas show in Finsbury Park in 1963 but it turned up 51 years later in America and somebody bought that guitar for innocently for 175 dollars.”</p><p> Similarly, earlier this year, Steve Vai&#39;s long-lost &#39;Swiss Cheese&#39; guitar used in the music video for David Lee Roth&#39;s &#39;Yankee Rose&#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/steve-vais-long-lost-swiss-cheese-guitar-used-in-david-lee-roth-music-video-recovered-after-36-years-3381849">was recovered after 36 years</a> .</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/hundreds-contact-global-search-for-paul-mccartneys-missing-1961-hofner-guitar-3492847">Hundreds contact global search for Paul McCartney&#39;s missing 1961 Höfner guitar</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
